WebProxy Settings for Git
git config --global https.proxy https://webproxy.atdesk.com:8080
git config --global http.proxy http://webproxy.atdesk.com:8080

--

Check the proxy settings
git config --global --get http.proxy

--

Shell verification of proxy
export http_proxy="http://webproxy.ssmb.com:8080/"

--

Remove SSL Verify
git config --global http.sslverify false

--

While Cloning a public repo add the username in front of it
For Ex. - git clone https://subodhp@github.com/tsuna/contextswitch.git

--

To add a newly edited file to git master repo online
git add <<new/updated file>>
git commit -m "comment"
git remote rm master
git remote add master https://subodhp@github.com/rb36135/citihpc-grid-tools.git --> for particular master branch, change the username, this is one time procedure only.
git push master
or
git push -f master

--

If file is removed
git rm <<file name>>
git commit -m "comment"
git remote add master https://subodhp@github.com/rb36135/citihpc-grid-tools.git --> for particular master branch, change the username
git push master
or
git push -f master

--

status
git status
git diff

--

Do not do this! unless you want to reinitialize the git repo
Reinitialize .git directory only under the subdirectories.
rm -rf .git
git init
git add *
git commit -m "comment"
git remote add master <<URL>>
git push master
or
git push -f master

--

To increase the GIT buffer, if getting RPC error
git config --global http.postBuffer 2M

--
